\begin{abstract}
We introduce \textbf{Chemathematics}, a new mathematical discipline that establishes chemistry as a branch of pure mathematics. Starting from five fundamental axioms, we derive all chemical properties using graph theory, algebraic topology, spectral theory, and homological algebra. Key results include: resonance energy as a topological invariant of the resonance graph, aromaticity as ring current in bond order space, and chemical reactivity from graph eigenvectors. This framework eliminates the need for quantum mechanical calculations and empirical parameters for a wide class of chemical systems. All results are constructive, computable, and open.
\end{abstract}

