\section{Computational Methods}

\subsection{Resonance Structure Enumeration}
The number of resonance structures for a given molecular graph is computed via backtracking with pruning. For a graph with \( m \) bonds, the worst-case complexity is \( O(2^m) \), but typical benzenoids scale as \( O(\theta^{n/2}) \) where \( \theta \) is the golden ratio.

\subsection{Spectral Computation}
Eigenvalues and eigenvectors are computed using standard LAPACK routines via NumPy. For graphs with \( n \leq 1000 \), this is practically instant.

\subsection{Homology Computation}
Simplicial homology is computed via boundary matrix reduction over \( \R \). The complexity is \( O(N^3) \) where \( N \) is the number of resonance structures (typically \( N \leq 10^4 \)).

