\section*{Glossary}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Molecular Graph}: A labeled graph representing atoms (vertices) and bonds (edges)
    \item \textbf{Resonance Structure}: An integer assignment of bond orders satisfying valence constraints
    \item \textbf{Arrow Push}: Movement of one electron pair between resonance structures
    \item \textbf{Resonance Graph}: Graph whose vertices are resonance structures, edges connect structures differing by one arrow push
    \item \textbf{Resonance Homology}: Homology groups of the clique complex of the resonance graph
    \item \textbf{Betti Number}: Dimension of a homology group; β₁ counts independent cycles in resonance space
    \item \textbf{Ring Current}: Measure of electron circulation in a ring, from bond order variance
    \item \textbf{NICS}: Nucleus-Independent Chemical Shift (aromaticity measure); negative = aromatic
    \item \textbf{Fukui Index}: Reactivity measure from frontier orbital densities (f⁻ for electrophiles, f⁺ for nucleophiles)
    \item \textbf{Graph Laplacian}: Matrix \( L = D - A \) for spectral analysis; eigenvalues determine connectivity
    \item \textbf{Effective Cycle Length}: Sum of weighted cycle lengths in resonance graph, proportional to resonance energy
    \item \textbf{Parity Conservation}: Invariant \( \Ztwo \)-grading on resonance structures of bipartite graphs
    \item \textbf{Coarse-graining Functor}: Map from atomic graphs to residue-level graphs preserving homology
\end{itemize}

